Sentencas: Cerium-gadolinium oxide is a promising material for electrolytes of intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs) due to its high electrical conductivity at relatively lower temperatures of 400-700 degrees C. However, a high sintering temperature of up to 1550 degrees C is typically required to produce dense CGO electrolyte, eventually leading to an interfacial interdiffusion between the electrolyte and electrode components as well as generate a highly resistive interface which reduces ionic conductivity.
Titulo: Anode supported micro-tubular SOFC fabricated with mixed particle size electrolyte via phase-inversion technique

Sentencas: Lowering the sintering temperature of the electrolyte will greatly benefit the fabrication of SOFCs.
Titulo: Anode supported micro-tubular SOFC fabricated with mixed particle size electrolyte via phase-inversion technique

Sentencas: This study examines the effectiveness of introducing nano size CGO particles as an approach to get dense CGO electrolyte at lower sintering temperature.
Titulo: Anode supported micro-tubular SOFC fabricated with mixed particle size electrolyte via phase-inversion technique

Sentencas: A series of dope suspensions with 0-50% nano size loading were prepared to observe rheology and measure viscosity.
Titulo: Anode supported micro-tubular SOFC fabricated with mixed particle size electrolyte via phase-inversion technique

Sentencas: Then, 30% loading was selected and casting into flat sheet via phase-inversion technique.
Titulo: Anode supported micro-tubular SOFC fabricated with mixed particle size electrolyte via phase-inversion technique

Sentencas: The flat sheet was characterized by morphology, surface roughness and mechanical strength tests.
Titulo: Anode supported micro-tubular SOFC fabricated with mixed particle size electrolyte via phase-inversion technique

Sentencas: The suspension was extruded into dual-layer hollow fiber (DLHF) as well.
Titulo: Anode supported micro-tubular SOFC fabricated with mixed particle size electrolyte via phase-inversion technique

Sentencas: The electrolyte/anode dual-layer hollow fibers (DLHFs) half-cell of micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cells (MTSOFCs) were prepared via phase inversion based co-extrusion/co-sintering technique.
Titulo: Anode supported micro-tubular SOFC fabricated with mixed particle size electrolyte via phase-inversion technique

Sentencas: The developed half-cell was characterized by morphological and gas tightness tests which further compared them with fully micron ones.
Titulo: Anode supported micro-tubular SOFC fabricated with mixed particle size electrolyte via phase-inversion technique

Sentencas: The results show that the incorporation of 30% nanoparticle yielded to dense and tight CGO layers sintered at temperature 1450 degrees C, which about 50 degrees C lower than those reported previously for 100% micron particles.
Titulo: Anode supported micro-tubular SOFC fabricated with mixed particle size electrolyte via phase-inversion technique

Sentencas: The I V measurements demonstrated the maximum power density of 0.66 Wcm(-2) at temperatures 500 degrees C using 100% H-2 as fuel.
Titulo: Anode supported micro-tubular SOFC fabricated with mixed particle size electrolyte via phase-inversion technique

Sentencas: Therefore, this approach is able to reduce the energy cost for the microstructural control of the prepared fiber and thus is recommended for the fabrication of low-cost dual-layer hollow fiber micro tubular SOFCs.
Titulo: Anode supported micro-tubular SOFC fabricated with mixed particle size electrolyte via phase-inversion technique
